com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Class BrowserContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.BrowserContext

  • public final class BrowserContext
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes context of a Browser instance. Provides path to the directory where Chromium data files such as cookies, history, cache will be stored and provides access to context level functionality such as NetworkService. Two Browser instances with same BrowserContext will share session cookies and cache files.
    描述浏览器实例的上下文。提供指向将存储Chromium数据文件（如cookie，历史记录，缓存）的目录的路径，并提供对上下文级别功能（如NetworkService）的访问。具有相同BrowserContext的两个Browser实例将共享会话cookie和缓存文件。

      • getAcceptLanguage

        public java.lang.String getAcceptLanguage()
        Returns a string that represents Accept-Language request-header field. This field restricts the set of natural languages that are preferred as a response to the request. For example: "da, en-gb;q=0.8, en;q=0.7".

        The default Accept-Language is "en-us".

        返回一个表示“接受语言”请求标头字段的字符串。该字段限制了首选自然语言集作为对请求的响应。例如：“ da，en-gb; q = 0.8，en; q = 0.7”。默认的接受语言为“ zh-cn”。
        See Also:
        W3 Documentation.

      • setAcceptLanguage

        public void setAcceptLanguage(java.lang.String acceptLanguage)
        Configures the accept language. If you don't provide an accept-Language value using this method then a default accept language will be used. The default Accept-Language is en-us.

        For example, fr, en-gb;q=0.8, en;q=0.7 would mean: "I prefer French, but will accept British English and other types of English." Note, that all languages which are assigned a quality factor greater than 0 are acceptable.

        配置接受语言。如果您不使用此方法提供accept-Language值，则将使用默认的接受语言。默认的接受语言为en-us。例如，fr，en-gb; q = 0.8，en; q = 0.7表示：“我更喜欢法语，但会接受英式英语和其他类型的英语。”请注意，所有被分配了大于0的品质因数的语言都是可以接受的。
        Parameters:
        acceptLanguage - a new string that represents the "Accept-Language" HTTP header value. -代表“ Accept-Language” HTTP标头值的新字符串。
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when acceptLanguage is null or empty.
        Since:
        6.19
        See Also:
        W3 Documentation.
